==Latin==
===Demonstrative Pronoun & Adjective===
(<i>'''iste'''</i> ''m'', '''ista''' ''f'', '''istud''' ''n'')
# "That (near you)" (''referring to a person or thing away from the speaker but close to the listener'').
# "That (infamous person or thing of yours)" (''used disparagingly'').

====Declension====
Irregular: similar to first and second declensions but with singular genitives ending in "-&#299;us" and singular datives ending in "-&#299;".
